On Sunday, Ramaphosa issued an immediate travel ban on people from high-risk countries affected by the coronavirus. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Transport, Fikile Mbalula, gave an update on the travel ban pronounced by the President Cyril Ramaphosa. On Sunday, Ramaphosa issued an immediate travel ban on people from high-risk countries affected by the coronavirus. South African citizens have also been advised to refrain from all forms of travel. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.